label: ZHC5010
description: FUGA Wall 4-way Switch with LED + Relay
info_overview:
ZHC5010 is a wall switch module with Z-Wave communication. The module contains four buttons, four LEDs, a built-in relay switch and is designed to fit into a standard LK FUGA® wall box (one-module format). The ZHC5010 Wall Switch allows you to control the local load as well as Z-Wave connected devices in up to four additional Z-Wave groups.

Configuration updated: 2017-12-10, firmware 2.03
info_inclusion: Place your primary controller in Adding Mode by following the manufacturer's instructions, then activate the add mode on the device by triple-clicking the upper left button on the module, or by triple-clicking the little button in the middle of the module (hidden behind the small plastic cover). Adding Mode is indicated by blinking of upper left LED until the timeout occurs after 10 seconds or the module has been added in the network.
info_exclusion:
Follow the inclusion procedures; the device is removed in the same manner, when the controller is in Removing Mode.

Factory reset:

ZHC5010 can be factory reset by pressing the small button in the middle of the module (normally covered by small plastic cover) for at least 10 seconds. Remove the middle plastic cover by means of a small screwdriver, and press the small button for at least 10 seconds, until all the LEDs lights up. Please use this procedure only when the network primary controller is missing or otherwise inoperable.

parameters.label: Relay mode
parameters.description: How built-in relay is controlled
parameters.overview: This parameter configures which of the buttons that shall control the built-in relay, or if the relay only will be activated for one second, each time button #1 is used.

options.label: Relay is controlled by button #1
options.overview: Relay is controlled by button #1 or by upper paddle when pair mode is active

options.label: Relay is controlled by button #2
options.overview: Relay is controlled by button #2 or by upper paddle when pair mode is active

options.label: Relay is controlled by button #3
options.overview: Relay is controlled by button #3 or by lower paddle when pair mode is active

options.label: Relay is controlled by button #4
options.overview: Relay is controlled by button #4 or by lower paddle when pair mode is active

options.label: Relay is activated for one second, button #1
options.overview: Relay is activated for one second and is controlled by button #1 or by upper paddle when pair mode is active

options.label: Relay is activated for half a second, button #2
options.overview: Relay is activated for half a second and is controlled by button #2 or by upper paddle when pair mode is active.

options.label: Relay is activated for half a second, button #3
options.overview: Relay is activated for half a second and is controlled by button #3 or by lower paddle when pair mode is active.

options.label: Relay is activated for half a second, button #4
options.overview: Relay is activated for half a second and is controlled by button #4 or by lower paddle when pair mode is active.

options.label: Relay follows the state of button #1
options.overview: Relay follows the state of button #1; when button is down the relay is on and when button is released the relay is off. Incoming button command messages will result in a short activation of the relay.

options.label: Relay follows the state of button #2
options.overview: Relay follows the state of button #2; when button is down the relay is on and when button is released the relay is off. Incoming button command messages will result in a short activation of the relay.

options.label: Relay follows the state of button #3
options.overview: Relay follows the state of button #3; when button is down the relay is on and when button is released the relay is off. Incoming button command messages will result in a short activation of the relay.

options.label: Relay follows the state of button #4
options.overview: Relay follows the state of button #4; when button is down the relay is on and when button is released the relay is off. Incoming button command messages will result in a short activation of the relay.

options.label: Relay is controlled by commands to root device
options.overview: Relay is only controlled by commands sent to the root device. Commands to the root device will not be forwarded to device 1.

parameters.label: Indicator mode.
parameters.description: set the current light level for the actual LED or the level value can be stored
parameters.overview: When ZHC5010 receives an Indicator Set message, then the received value can be used only to set the current light level for the actual LED or the level value can be stored and will then be used for subsequent internal activations.

options.label: Indicator Set used to control the LED.
options.overview: Indicator Set level values are only used to control the LED.

options.label: Indicator Set values and internal activations.
options.overview: Indicator Set level values and also used by internal LED activations. (Default)

parameters.label: Scene notification offset.
parameters.description: Scene sequence numbers transmitted by Central Scene notifications.
parameters.overview:
Configure the scene sequence numbers that will be transmitted by Central Scene notifications.

Button #1 will send scene [value], button #2 will send scene [value] + 1, button #3 will send scene [value] + 2, button #4 will send scene [value] + 3. (Default = 1)

options.label: Send scene value for button #
options.overview: Button #1 will send scene [value], button #2 will send scene [value] + 1, button #3 will send scene [value] + 2, button #4 will send scene [value] + 3. (Default = 1)

parameters.label: Disable House Cleaning.
parameters.description: Disable House Cleaning Mode.
parameters.overview: This parameter is able to enable or disable the so-called “House Cleaning Mode”, where ZHC5010 is able send a dimming command in order to set the level of the lights to 100%.

options.label: House Cleaning Mode is enabled
options.overview: House Cleaning Mode is enabled (Default)

parameters.label: Multilevel Switch (button #1) Disabled/Enabled
parameters.description: Multilevel Switch on single press for device 1 (button #1)

options.label: Disabled
options.overview: Disabled – When single pressing the button, nodes associated to group 6 won’t be switched.

options.label: Enabled
options.overview: Enabled – When single pressing the button, nodes associated to group 6 will be switched between the configured upper and lower switch values. (Default)

parameters.label: Non-secure commands for AG in logical device 1
parameters.description: Allow sending non-secure commands to association members if added securely
parameters.overview:
If ZHC5010 is included secure, this parameter allows sending messages on keypresses to non-secure devices (e.g. pre-gen5 relays).

If ZHC5010 is included non-secure, this parameter has no function.

0         : No commands sent unencrypted (default)

1  (0x01) : Bit#1. Not used.

2  (0x02) : Bit#2. Send BASICREPORT to association group 2 unencrypted.

4  (0x04) : Bit#3. Send BASICSET to association group 3 unencrypted.

8  (0x08) : Bit#4. Send BINARYSWITCHSET to association group 4 unencrypted.

16 (0x10) : Bit#5. Send BINARYTOGGLESWITCHSET to association group 5 unencrypted.

32 (0x20) : Bit#6. Send MULTILEVELSWITCH to association group 6 unencrypted.
